  "response": "Based on available information, working as a software engineer at Cisco Systems in Bangalore typically involves:\n\nTechnologies:\n- Cloud computing platforms (AWS, Azure)\n- Software-defined networking\n- Network virtualization\n- Cybersecurity technologies\n- DevOps tools\n- Programming languages like Java, Python, C++\n- Kubernetes, Docker containers\n- Machine learning and AI technologies\n\nWork Environment:\n- Large campus with modern facilities\n- Collaborative team-based culture\n- Opportunities for skill development\n- Global exposure working with international teams\n- Competitive compensation and benefits\n\nLearning & Growth:\n- Internal training programs\n- Technical certification support\n- Cross-functional project opportunities\n- Mentorship programs\n- Access to latest technological resources\n\nKey Focus Areas:\n- Network infrastructure solutions\n- Enterprise networking technologies\n- Security software development\n- Routing and switching technologies\n- Collaboration platforms\n\nPlease note that specific details can vary depending on individual teams and current projects. For the most accurate and current information, I recommend checking Cisco's official website or speaking directly with current employees.\n\nThis overview is based on general publicly available information about Cisco's Bangalore office and typical software engineering roles.",
